<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 9:56AM EST  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...PATCHY BLACK ICE THIS MORNING AND EARLY AFTERNOON ACROSS PARTS
OF THE MOUNTAINS OF NORTH CAROLINA AND NORTHEAST GEORGIA...
Temperatures remain below freezing this morning and may result in
patches of black ice on untreated and secondary roads across
mountain locations that received snow yesterday. Black ice could
result in slippery spots on some roadways. Temperatures will rise
above freezing between late morning and early afternoon, permitting
melting and drying.
Use caution if driving in the North Carolina mountains or
adjacent locales in northeast Georgia.</description>
